HEADWORD: Deletion
<hw>De*le"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>deletio</ets>, fr. <ets>delere</ets>. See <er>Delete</er>.]</ety>
<def>Act of deleting, blotting out, or erasing; destruction.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A total <qex>deletion</qex> of every person of the opposing
party.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deletitious</ent>⟦br⟧
